<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-496-773  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 496 773.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  August 13 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>SPA to host Industry Forum at Business Computing '90. (SoftwarePublisher's Association to hold forum at trade show)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gold, Steve.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Software Publishers AssociationConferences and MeetingsSoftware PublishersConsortiaFrance.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>SPA TO HOST INDUSTRY FORUM AT BUSINESS COMPUTING '90 PARIS, FRANCE, 1990 AUG13 (NB) -- The Software Publisher's Association (SPA) has announced it ishosting an SPA Industry Forum meeting at the Business Computing '90 show,scheduled to be held at London's Olympia on September 24 and 25.andM;Keynote speakers at the SPA event will be David Pritchard, European generalmanager of Claris International and Bernard Vergnes, vice president ofMicrosoft Europe.andM;Session topics scheduled for the forum include: European distribution,networks, Apple Mac System 7.0 software, European and American market trends,the fight against piracy, and starting a software business.andM;Anyone interested in registering for the SPA Industry Forum should contactthe SPA in Paris at +33-1-4692-2703/04 or in Washington (DC) at+1-202-452-1600.andM;(Steve Gold/19900813/Press andamp; Public Contact: Pascale Chatelain, manager -European affairs, SPA - Tel: +33-1-4692-2703/04)</TEXT></DOC>